# Design Systems Checklist

Source: https://tylercoderre.com/projects/design-systems-checklist.html by Tyler Coderre

## Design Language

This is how your product "talks" to people. It's the look, feel, and flow that makes everything feel connected. When it all works together, users don't have to think too hard.

### Brand

Your brand is more than a logo or a cool name. It's what you stand for and how people remember you. It should guide every decision you make.

- [ ] **Vision** - Why you exist, what you believe in, and what direction you're going.
- [ ] **Design Principles** - Your go-to rules for making design choices. They help keep your work focused and clear.
- [ ] **Tone of Voice** - How you sound when you talk to users. This helps make sure people always know it's you speaking, no matter where they are. (WCAG: 3.1, 3.1.1–3.1.6)
- [ ] **Terminology** - Pick the right words and use them the same way across your product. This keeps things simple and clear. (WCAG: 3.1.3–3.1.6)
- [ ] **Brand Assets** - Things like your logo, fonts, colors, and icons. Using them the same way everywhere helps your product look and feel like one solid thing.

### Guidelines

You lose if your product feels different every time someone uses it. Clear guidelines help your team stay on the same page and create a consistent experience.

- [ ] **Accessibility** - Make sure everyone can use your product. Use clear color contrast, logical layout, and support for screen readers and other tools. (WCAG: All Criteria)
- [ ] **Writing Guidelines** - Set the rules for how you write. Things like grammar, tone, and word choice should all match. (WCAG: 3.1, 3.1.1–3.1.6)
- [ ] **Microcopy Guidelines** - Short UI text like button labels, error messages, and tooltips should follow consistent rules. (WCAG: 3.1.2–3.1.4)
- [ ] **Terminology** - Pick the right words once, and use them everywhere. This avoids confusion and keeps things running smoothly. (WCAG: 3.1.3, 3.1.4, 3.1.6)
- [ ] **Internationalization** - Plan for translation. Set up rules for handling different languages, longer words, and right-to-left text when needed. (WCAG: 3.1, 3.1.1–3.1.6)

