## Maintenance

Design systems aren't "set it and forget it" projects. They need regular updates, clear planning, and open feedback loops.

### Documentation

- [ ] **Design System Principles** - List core values and decision-making rules.
- [ ] **Getting Started** - Simple guide for setting up and using the system.
- [ ] **Design Best Practices** - Smart ways to use the system in your design tool.
- [ ] **Development Best Practices** - Technical do's and don'ts.
- [ ] **Component Anatomy** - Break down components so users know which parts can be changed.
- [ ] **Component Properties** - List all supported properties in design file and code.
- [ ] **Component Composition Examples** - Show how smaller components combine into complex ones.
- [ ] **Sandbox Product Example** - Working example showing components in context.
- [ ] **Browser and/or OS Support** - Document officially supported browsers and operating systems.
- [ ] **Release Cycle** - Set a clear release schedule for major changes.

### Libraries

- [ ] **When to Build** - When to build locally vs adding to the core system.
- [ ] **Horizontal and Vertical Libraries** - Shared across products vs built for a single product.
- [ ] **Library Expectations** - Basic standards for code quality, documentation, naming, maintenance.
- [ ] **Release Cycle Alignment** - Local libraries stay in sync with main system updates.

### Processes

- [ ] **Decision Log** - Track design and development decisions and their reasoning.
- [ ] **Roadmap** - Plan big-picture goals, not just day-to-day requests.
- [ ] **Stakeholder Mapping** - Identify who uses the system and how.
- [ ] **Analytics** - Track doc site visits, design tool usage, feedback to understand what needs attention.
- [ ] **Ongoing Support "Shifts"** - Take turns handling questions and requests.
- [ ] **SLA** - Set clear expectations on response times for bugs, questions, feature requests.

### Community

- [ ] **Support Channels** - Clear channels for support, split by platform if needed.
- [ ] **Templates** - Easy bug report and feature request templates.
- [ ] **Regular Updates** - Share updates to keep community in the loop.
- [ ] **Office Hours** - Bookable time slots for teams to talk through problems.

### Contribution

- [ ] **House Rules for the System** - How your team works around design and development decisions.
- [ ] **Contribution Guidelines** - Step-by-step instructions for setting up and testing changes.
- [ ] **Feature Proposal Template** - Guide for new feature proposals with design mockups and impact assessment.
- [ ] **Engagement** - Shout out contributors in release notes. Recognize their effort.
